          • [ - ] Big_Boss - member since 19-Nov-16

            @Zoltan Here is a lesson for you. Your front three do not have to be in perfect sync to get the job done. The fact that they're running away with the Premier League and are current World and CL champions clearly shows that it's their team effort and solid defense that brought them where they are now. Tunnelvisioning into one away loss in Napoli is a poor argument to make to prove that Liverpool is not ready to tackle the remaining elite teams in Europe. Why? They've done it before and are more experienced now. In addition, they have benchplayers who can score. Wijnaldum and Origi against Barcelona for instance. In football anything can happen, but you have to give credit where it's due and acknowledge that Liverpool is arguably the team to beat in Europe, thanks to their pedigree they've been building in just 2 years. And nobody is comparing Norwich to the CL elite teams. The players know it will be tougher in the Champions League, so you again have no point to make.
